HEADWORD: Sphygmograph
<hw>Sphyg"mo*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/<?/<?/
the pulse + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An
instrument which, when applied over an artery, indicates graphically the
movements or character of the pulse. See <er>Sphygmogram</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

